<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF59FF12A7ADF9F7FBEBDEAA" lastPageId="193" lastPageNumber="194" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF59FF13A7ADF9F7FEE9DA33" blockId="192.[189,303,1560,1586]" box="[189,303,1560,1586]" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF59FF13A7ADF9F7FEE9DA33" bold="true" box="[189,303,1560,1586]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A7ADF9F7FEE9DA33" bold="true" box="[189,303,1560,1586]" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF59FF13A7ADF9A7FB44DB3B" blockId="192.[188,1400,1607,1850]" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">
In a key to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A6F3F9A8FC8FDA63" authority="Kraepelin, 1895" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1895" box="[483,841,1607,1634]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Stygophrynus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A6F3F9A8FD45DA60" box="[483,643,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">Stygophrynus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF59FF13A59AF9A8FC8FDA63" author="Kraepelin K." box="[650,841,1607,1634]" firstAuthor="Kraepelin" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" pagination="3 - 53" part="13" refId="ref150262" refString="Kraepelin K. 1895. Revision der Tarantuliden Fabr. Verhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg 13: 3 - 53." title="Revision der Tarantuliden Fabr" type="journal article" year="1895">Kraepelin, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF59FF13A445F9A8FB94DA60" author="Gravely F. H." box="[853,1106,1607,1634]" firstAuthor="Gravely" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" page="443" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" pagination="433 - 455" part="11" refId="ref149126" refString="Gravely F. H. 1915 b. A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi). Records of the Indian Museum 11: 433 - 455." title="A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi)" type="journal article" year="1915" yearSuffix="b">Gravely (1915b: 443)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the “armature of [the] hand [tibia] of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A6D5F983FD8FDA84" box="[453,585,1643,1670]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A6D5F983FD8FDA84" box="[453,585,1643,1670]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of two long dorsal spines and one ventral one only” whereas, for all other species, 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF59FF13A6A6F960FD70DAAB" author="Gravely F. H." box="[438,694,1679,1706]" firstAuthor="Gravely" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" page="443" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" pagination="433 - 455" part="11" refId="ref149126" refString="Gravely F. H. 1915 b. A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi). Records of the Indian Museum 11: 433 - 455." title="A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi)" type="journal article" year="1915" yearSuffix="b">Gravely (1915b: 443)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the “hand [is] armed above and below with one long spine succeeded by a series of short spines which increase in length distally”. The former spine configuration is typical of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A6E0F937FDB7DAF3" authorityName="Quintero" authorityYear="1986" box="[496,625,1752,1778]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Charinidae</taxonomicName>
and the latter is typical of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A4B2F937FBF2DAF3" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[930,1076,1752,1778]" class="Arachnida" family="Charontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Charontidae</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A3E2F937FAB0DAF3" box="[1266,1398,1752,1778]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A3E2F937FAB0DAF3" box="[1266,1398,1752,1778]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a charinid. 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF59FF13A64FF913FD99DB17" author="Gravely F. H." box="[351,607,1787,1814]" firstAuthor="Gravely" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" page="444" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" pagination="433 - 455" part="11" refId="ref149126" refString="Gravely F. H. 1915 b. A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi). Records of the Indian Museum 11: 433 - 455." title="A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi)" type="journal article" year="1915" yearSuffix="b">Gravely (1915b: 444)</bibRefCitation>
further noted that 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A450F913FC01DB17" box="[832,967,1788,1814]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A450F913FC01DB17" box="[832,967,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses three dorsal spines on the pedipalp tarsus: “the finger is armed above with three-minute tooth-like spinules”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF59FF12A7ADF88DFEFEDDD8" blockId="192.[188,1399,1889,2025]" lastBlockId="193.[189,1401,265,473]" lastPageId="193" lastPageNumber="194" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">
Specimens from the vicinity of the type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A41EF88DFC55DB7D" box="[782,915,1890,1916]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A41EF88DFC55DB7D" box="[782,915,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., AMCC [LP 12168, 12169]) exhibit characters consistent with 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF59FF13A6E5F869FD0ADBA0" author="Gravely F. H." box="[501,716,1926,1953]" firstAuthor="Gravely's" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" pagination="433 - 455" part="11" refId="ref149126" refString="Gravely F. H. 1915 b. A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi). Records of the Indian Museum 11: 433 - 455." title="A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi)" type="journal article" year="1915" yearSuffix="b">Gravely’s (1915b)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A47EF868FC35DBA1" box="[878,1011,1926,1953]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A47EF868FC35DBA1" box="[878,1011,1926,1953]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g., high numbers of spines on the pedipalp patella and three spines on the pedipalp tarsus, characters which are also diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A7ADF820FEFDDBE9" authorityName="Rahmadi, Harvey &amp; Kojima" authorityYear="2010" box="[189,315,1998,2025]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yayukae">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A7ADF820FEFDDBE9" box="[189,315,1998,2025]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">S. yayukae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A6DCF820FD94DBE9" box="[460,594,1998,2025]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A6DCF820FD94DBE9" box="[460,594,1998,2025]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF59FF13A4A0F820FBE8DBE9" authorityName="Rahmadi, Harvey &amp; Kojima" authorityYear="2010" box="[944,1070,1998,2025]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yayukae">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A4A0F820FBE8DBE9" box="[944,1070,1998,2025]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">S. yayukae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF59FF13A32DF821FAF9DBE9" author="Rahmadi C. &amp; Kojima J." box="[1085,1343,1998,2024]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rahmadi" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Arachnology" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" pagination="475 - 484" part="38" refId="ref152642" refString="Rahmadi C. &amp; Kojima J. - i. 2010. Whip spiders of the genus Sarax in the Papuan region, with description of two new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Journal of Arachnology 38: 475 - 484. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / Ha 09 - 95.1" title="Whip spiders of the genus Sarax in the Papuan region, with description of two new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">
Rahmadi 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF59FF13A3BFF820FB2CDBE9" box="[1199,1258,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
also suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF58FF12A677FEE6FE2DDD22" box="[359,491,265,291]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF58FF12A677FEE6FE2DDD22" box="[359,491,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be a charinid. The 
<typeStatus id="D8511CC1FF58FF12A401FEE6FCBEDD22" box="[785,888,265,291]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF58FF12A48BFEE6FBD9DD22" box="[923,1055,265,291]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF58FF12A48BFEE6FBD9DD22" box="[923,1055,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be examined to confirm the synonymy; however, 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF58FF12A6F8FEC2FD2ADD46" author="Rahmadi C. &amp; Kojima J." box="[488,748,301,328]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rahmadi" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Arachnology" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="475 - 484" part="38" refId="ref152642" refString="Rahmadi C. &amp; Kojima J. - i. 2010. Whip spiders of the genus Sarax in the Papuan region, with description of two new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae). Journal of Arachnology 38: 475 - 484. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / Ha 09 - 95.1" title="Whip spiders of the genus Sarax in the Papuan region, with description of two new species (Amblypygi: Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">
Rahmadi 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF58FF12A54BFEC1FD48DD46" box="[603,654,301,327]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested it may be lost. Until that is established with certainty, it is appropriate to transfer 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF58FF12A56CFEBDFCC2DD6A" box="[636,772,337,364]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF58FF12A56CFEBDFCC2DD6A" box="[636,772,337,364]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF58FF12A4B8FEBDFC2ADD6D" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[936,1004,338,364]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF58FF12A4B8FEBDFC2ADD6D" box="[936,1004,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Sarax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the evidence available. Due to the lack of characters in the literature allowing a precise identification of the species and the lack of type material, it is suggested here that the species is a nomen dubium until further clarification of its taxonomy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF58FF12A7ADFDEFFBEBDEAA" blockId="193.[187,1399,512,684]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF58FF12A7ADFDEFFEB9DE1A" author="Quintero D., Jr." box="[189,383,512,539]" editor="Eberhard, W. &amp; Lubin, Y. D. &amp; Robinson B. C." firstAuthor="Quintero" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington D. C." pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="203 - 212" part="1983" refId="ref152451" refString="Quintero D., Jr. 1986. Revision de la clasification de Amblypygidos pulvinados: Creacion de subordenes, una neuva familia y un nuevo genero con tres nuevas especies (Arachnida: Amblypygi). In: Eberhard, W. G, Lubin, Y. D. &amp; Robinson B. C. (eds) Proceedings of the 9 th International Congress of Arachnology, Panama 1983: 203 - 212. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington D. C." title="Revision de la clasification de Amblypygidos pulvinados: Creacion de subordenes, una neuva familia y un nuevo genero con tres nuevas especies (Arachnida: Amblypygi)" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Proceedings of the 9 th International Congress of Arachnology, Panama" year="1986">Quintero (1986)</bibRefCitation>
provided two SEM images of the pedipalp patella and tarsus of a specimen from Sebesi, 
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FF58FF12A60AFDCAFEB9DE3E" box="[282,383,549,575]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FFDE2F3FF58FF12A69CFDCAFDC7DE3E" box="[396,513,549,575]" name="Indonesia" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, identified as 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF58FF12A5B8FDCAFCF6DE3E" box="[680,816,549,575]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF58FF12A5B8FDCAFCF6DE3E" box="[680,816,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the spination of that specimen differs considerably from what was described and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF58FF12A442FDA6FBD5DE65" author="Gravely F. H." box="[850,1043,585,612]" firstAuthor="Gravely" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="433 - 455" part="11" refId="ref149126" refString="Gravely F. H. 1915 b. A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi). Records of the Indian Museum 11: 433 - 455." title="A revision of the Oriental subfamilies of Tarantulidae (order Pedipalpi)" type="journal article" year="1915" yearSuffix="b">Gravely (1915b)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF58FF12A351FDA6FB03DE62" box="[1089,1221,585,611]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Neocharon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moultoni">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF58FF12A351FDA6FB03DE62" box="[1089,1221,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">S. moultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen illustrated by 
